  "body": "```\r\nkubectl set image --local -f busybox.yaml busybox=busybox:1.26 -o yaml\r\nerror: unable to connect to a server to handle \"deployments\": Get https://127.0.0.1:8443/api: dial tcp 127.0.0.1:8443: getsockopt: connection refused\r\n```\r\nIt tries to contact the api server for the discovery docs and fails because no api server is running. Could `kubectl` first look in its local cache if it's passed --local?\r\n\r\n@kubernetes/sig-cli-bugs ",
